==English==

===Etymology===
From {{bor|en|fr|galop}}; named after the fastest running gait of a horse (see ''[[gallop]]''), a shortened version of the original term ''galoppade''.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# A [[lively]] [[French]] [[country dance]] of the nineteenth century, a forerunner of the [[polka]], combining a [[glissade]] with a [[chassé]] on alternate feet, usually in a fast 2/4 time.
# The [[music]] for a dance of this kind.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|pres_ptc2=galopped|past2=galopped}}

# To dance the galop.

